{{Infobox football league | name = Botola 2 | image = | pixels = | country = [[Morocco]] | confed = [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] | founded = 1996 | first = | folded = | divisions = | teams = 16 | feeds = | promotion = [[Botola]] | relegation = [[GNFA 1]] | levels = 2 | domest_cup = [[Coupe du Trône]] | confed_cup = [[CAF Confederation Cup]] | champions = [[Chabab Atlas Khénifra]] | season = [[2015-16 GNF 2]] | most_successful = [[FUS Rabat]](3) | tv = | website = | current = [[2017–18 Botola 2]] }}
'''Botola 2''' (, also known before as the ''Groupement National de Football 2''), is the second division of the [[Moroccan football league system|Moroccan football league]], behind the [[Botola]], the highest football league in Morocco. It features 19 teams across the country that compete for the top two positions in the competition which at the end of the season allows them promotion to the [[Botola]]. Each season as well, the 3 bottom teams are all relegated to the third-level, [[GNFA 1| Division Nationale]].
