{{Infobox organization |name = Game of Golf Institute (GOGI) |main_classification = [[Non-profit organization]] |headquarters = [[Sea Island, Georgia]] |founder = [[Derek V. Smith]] , [[Randy Myers (golf trainer)|Randy Myers]] Todd Anderson and Kristian Traylor |founded_date = 2011 |website = {{URL|http://www.mygogi.org/|www.mygogi.org}} }}
'''Game of Golf Institute (GOGI)''' is a [[501(c)(3)]] [[non-profit organization]] geared towards the growth of recreational [[golf]] through the use of technology and education.
== History == GOGI was founded in 2011 by [[Derek V. Smith]] and golf instructors Todd Anderson and [[Randy Myers (golf trainer)|Randy Myers]]. Co-founder Kristian Traylor joined GOGI in 2012.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Palmer |first=Chris |date=March–April 2012 |title=GOGI and Golf’s Future |url=http://www.editionduo.com/publication/?m=2525&l=1 |journal=Golf Georgia |publisher=GSGA |accessdate=9 April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media | people=Meyers, Randy | title=[http://www.golfchannel.com/media/morning-drive-randy-myers-interview/ Myers: Getting players fit in Sea Island] | medium=TV | location=USA | publisher=Golf Channel}}</ref>
== Products and Services == === Website === GOGI's website facilitates engagement and social sharing among recreational golfers, golf instructors and organizations (clubs, associations, courses) as well as game improvement using instructional videos, swing analysis and stats analysis.<ref>{{cite news | first=Steve | last=DiMeglio | title=Gogi Helps Golfers Get a Grip | work=Masters - Golf & Gear 2014 Special Edition | publisher=USA Today | date=1 April 2014 }}</ref>
=== Mobile Applications === GOGI's mobile applications are integrated with the GOGI website. GOGI's mobile applications allow users to access the website's features and instructional videos as well as enter and track golf scores, access golf tips, access the rules of golf, download practice drills and record and analyze golf swings using a [[smartphone]] or tablet computer.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.golfchannel.com/news/golftalkcentral/offerings-pga-merchandise-show/ |title = Offerings from the PGA Merchandise Show |last = Hoggard |first = Rex |publisher = Golf Channel |date = 27 January 2013 |website = Golf Channel|accessdate= 1 April 2014 }}</ref> Actions completed in the applications synchronize with the website.
