'''Marie-Louise Bévis''' (born 12 October 1972 in [[Morne-à-l'Eau]], [[Guadeloupe]]) is a retired French sprinter who specialized in the [[400 metres]].

She finished fifth at the [[1995 IAAF World Indoor Championships|1995 World Indoor Championships]],<ref name=bio>{{iaaf name|id=68182}}</ref> won the gold medal at the 1997 [[Jeux de la Francophonie]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/ic/fg.htm|title=Francophone Games|work=GBR Athletics|publisher=Athletics Weekly|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref> and the gold medal at the [[2001 Mediterranean Games]].<ref name=bio/> She also competed at the [[2000 European Athletics Indoor Championships|2000 European Indoor Championships]] without reaching the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maik-richter.de/results/indoor/europe/2000/f00_07.html|title=2000 European Indoor Championships, women's 400 metres qualification|publisher=Die Leichtatletik-Statistik-Seite|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref>

In the [[4 × 400 metres relay]] she finished sixth at the [[1993 World Championships in Athletics – Women's 4 x 400 metres relay|1993 World Championships]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/athletics/world/1993/Women_4x400m_Relay.html|title=Women 4x400m Relay World Championship 1993 Stuttgart (GER)|publisher=Todor Krastev|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref> and fifth at the [[2002 European Athletics Championships|2002 European Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/athletics/europe/2002/Women_4x400m_Relay.html|title=Women 4x400m Relay European Championships 2002 Munich (GER)|publisher=Todor Krastev|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref> She also competed at the [[1995 World Championships in Athletics – Women's 4 x 400 metres relay|1995 World Championships]] and the [[2003 World Championships in Athletics – Women's 4 × 400 metres relay|2003 World Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/athletics/world/1995/Women_4x400m_Relay.html|title=Women 4x400m Relay World Championship 1995 Goteborg (SWE)|publisher=Todor Krastev|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/athletics/world/2003/Women_4x400m_Relay.html|title=Women 4x400m Relay World Championship 2003 Paris (FRA)|publisher=Todor Krastev|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref>

Her personal best times are 11.89 seconds in the [[100 metres]], achieved in September 2003 in [[Saint-Florentin, Yonne|Saint-Florentin]]; 23.95 seconds in the [[200 metres]], achieved in May 2002 in [[Lisbon]]; and 52.06 seconds in the 400 metres, achieved in June 2003 in [[Nogent-sur-Marne]].<ref name=bio/>

